    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-20T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-20T08:00:00-05:00" n="712"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/544</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-20T13:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                    </date> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5:15 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> showed me <persName
                        corresp="#p_BSC1">Barclay</persName>’s despatch about your conference with
                    him about mines and the answer that <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Grey</persName>
                    telegraphed to <persName corresp="#p_BSC1">Barclay</persName> three days ago.
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Grey</persName> seemed puzzled and somewhat
                    surprised at our wish to exact from him a pledge which would give the Germans
                    license to use mines and bind the English not to use them. I understand that the
                    Hague convention of 1907 relating to laying of contact mines is not operative in
                    present war by reason of Article 7.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
